  "prompt": "What is a zero sum game?",
  "response": "A zero-sum game is a game, mathematical or economic model where the total gain of one player is exactly equal to the loss of another player. In other words, the sum of all outcomes must always be zero. This means that for one player to gain something, another player must lose an equivalent amount. It is a situation in which participants' gains or losses are exactly balanced by the corresponding losses or gains of the other participants. Zero-sum games are often used to model competitive situations where the interests of the participants are in direct opposition.",
